net.opentsdb.core

接口 DataPoint

  • 所有已知子接口:
    iRowSeq.Iterator
    所有已知实现类:
    AggregationIterator, Downsampler, ExpressionDataPoint, FillingDownsampler, MutableDataPoint, RollupSeq.RollupIterator

    public interface DataPoint
    Represents a single data point.

    Implementations of this interface aren't expected to be synchronized.

    • 方法概要

      所有方法 实例方法 抽象方法 
      限定符和类型 方法和说明
      double doubleValue()
      Returns the value of the this data point as a double.
      boolean isInteger()
      Tells whether or not the this data point is a value of integer type.
      long longValue()
      Returns the value of the this data point as a long.
      long timestamp()
      Returns the timestamp (in milliseconds) associated with this data point.
      double toDouble()
      Returns the value of the this data point as a double, even if it's a long.
      long valueCount()
      Represents the number of real values behind this data point when referring to a pre-aggregated and/or rolled up value.

    • 方法详细资料

      • timestamp

        long timestamp()
        Returns the timestamp (in milliseconds) associated with this data point.
        返回:
        A strictly positive, 32 bit integer.

      • isInteger

        boolean isInteger()
        Tells whether or not the this data point is a value of integer type.
        返回:
        true if the ith value is of integer type, false if it's of doubleing point type.

      • longValue

        long longValue()
        Returns the value of the this data point as a long.
        抛出:
        ClassCastException - if the isInteger() == false.

      • doubleValue

        double doubleValue()
        Returns the value of the this data point as a double.
        抛出:
        ClassCastException - if the isInteger() == true.

      • toDouble

        double toDouble()
        Returns the value of the this data point as a double, even if it's a long.
        返回:
        When isInteger() == false, this method returns the same thing as doubleValue(). Otherwise, it returns the same thing as longValue()'s return value casted to a double.

      • valueCount

        long valueCount()
        Represents the number of real values behind this data point when referring to a pre-aggregated and/or rolled up value.
        返回:
        The number of real values represented in this data point. Usually just 1 for raw values.
